| Priority | Area                   | Scenario                                            | What to verify                                                                                               |
| -------- | ---------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| P1       | Account creation       | Create new user with SSO and email                  | User account created successfully; user can log in and proceed to booking flow                               |
| P1       | Booking + Payment      | Happy path: book → pay → confirmation               | Exactly one booking + one successful payment; confirmation shows correct slot/provider; receipt state stored |
| P1       | Privacy leakage        | No PHI in logs/URLs/analytics/errors                | Inspect network calls, server logs (test env), client console, analytics p                         |
| P1       | Payment integrity      | Refresh/back/double-click after “Pay”               | No duplicate charges; booking not duplicated                                       |
| P1       | State consistency      | Payment succeeds but booking fails (and vice versa) | Correct user messaging; no inconsistent or “ghost” appointments                                              |
| P1       | Availability integrity | Two users book same slot concurrently               | Only one succeeds; the other receives clear error/state message with alternative slots                       |
| P1       | Authorization          | Patient A cannot access Patient B booking           | API + UI access blocked; IDs not enumerable; proper 403/404 responses                                        |
| P1       | Time handling          | Time zones + DST                                    | Slot displayed and stored correctly; reminders sent at correct time                                          |
| P1       | Payment failures       | Declines/timeouts                                   | Clear recovery path; booking not confirmed (or placed in safe pending state)                                 |
| P1       | Refunds                | Cancel → refund full/partial                        | Correct refund amount; proper status transitions, receipts, and audit trail                                  |
| P1       | Notifications          | Email/SMS confirmation content                      | No PHI exposure; correct time/location; links require authentication                                         |
| P2       | Input validation       | Edge fields (names, phone, DOB formats)             | Proper validation, localization handling, and clear error messages                                           |
| P2       | Password reset         | Forgot password                                     | Reset email sent correctly; user can reset password and sign in successfully afterward                       |

# I put account creation 1st cause without succcessful sign up/login no further action is possible, the user would be blocked
# Happy path scenario comes 2nd cause it ensures the flow works on the whole. 
# Privacy (PHI compliance) should be main priority so I'd put it 3rd after user submits any data of themselves -- 'cause adheres it is crucial for business
# All in all that is difficult to choose only 3 tests, f.e., validation (negative testing is super important here as well -- 
# let us say the person who is younger than 18 years old or with an invalid/expired CC or both patients doing something real-time situations are handled properly). 
